        "Famous players: Fischer, Kasparov, Tal all loved the Sicilian."
    ),
    "caro-kann": (
        "Caro-Kann Defence (1.e4 c6)\n\n"
        "Solid and reliable. Black prepares d5 without weakening the queenside. "
        "Less dynamic than the Sicilian but very solid. Favoured by positional players.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Karpov, Petrosian, Anand."
    ),
    "kings gambit": (
        "King's Gambit (1.e4 e5 2.f4)\n\n"
        "Aggressive Romantic-era opening. White sacrifices a pawn for rapid development "
        "and an attack on the f-file. Highly tactical — both sides must play precisely.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Morphy, Spassky, Tal."
    ),
    "queens gambit": (
        "Queen's Gambit (1.d4 d5 2.c4)\n\n"
        "Not a true gambit — if Black takes, White easily regains the pawn. "
        "Leads to solid, strategic play. Two main lines: QGA (accepted) and QGD (declined).\n\n"
        "Famous players: Karpov, Kramnik, Carlsen."
    ),
    "ruy lopez": (
        "Ruy Lopez / Spanish Opening (1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bb5)\n\n"
        "One of the oldest and most respected openings. White pressures the e5 pawn "
        "indirectly via the pin on the c6 knight. Enormous theory — played at the highest level.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Kasparov, Carlsen, Fischer."
    ),
    "french": (
        "French Defence (1.e4 e6)\n\n"
        "Black immediately prepares d5. Creates a solid pawn chain but can be passive. "
        "Main lines: Winawer, Classical, Advance, Exchange.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Korchnoi, Botvinnik, Short."
    ),
    "london": (
        "London System (1.d4 + 2.Nf3 + 3.Bf4)\n\n"
        "Simple, solid setup for White. Easy to learn, hard to blow up. "
        "Not the sharpest but very reliable — popular at all levels including top GMs.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Carlsen uses it regularly."
    ),
    "nimzo-indian": (
        "Nimzo-Indian Defence (1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 e6 3.Nc3 Bb4)\n\n"
        "Black pins White's knight and fights for the centre. One of the richest openings "
        "in chess — Black can win the bishop pair or get structural compensation.\n\n"
        "Famous players: Nimzowitsch, Kasparov, Kramnik."
    ),
}

def handle(text):
    tl = text.lower().strip()
    if not any(t in tl for t in TRIGGERS):
        return None
    for name, description in OPENINGS.items():
        if name in tl:
            return description
    return None

